From d1034095804738d27b0041c0b64c1cb335ceca9a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jason Gross <jason@theorem.dev>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 22:50:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 09/10] arm: ".word" emits a 32-bit datum (only x86 treats it
 as 16-bit)

tccasm.c groups the `.word` directive with `.short`, giving both
size = 2. That is the x86 convention (`.word` is 16 bits there), but on
ARM -- and in GNU as generally for ARM -- `.word` is a 32-bit datum.
Under the fork, every ARM `.word` was silently truncated to two bytes.

Found by the bootstrap. musl-1.1.24's a_crash() emits `.word 0xe7f000f0`
(the ARM permanently-undefined instruction) inline. Assembled as 2 bytes
instead of 4, it left the enclosing text section 2-byte misaligned; the
next inline function's 4-byte-aligned branch-fixup chain (linked through
the 24-bit branch immediate) then walked corrupted offsets, and tcc
SIGSEGV'd in decbranch/gsym_addr while compiling malloc.c. Discriminator:
an atomic sequence ending in a real `dmb` instruction assembled fine; the
same sequence ending in the `.word`-encoded crash did not -- isolating
the directive, not the codegen.

Split `.word` (size = 4 on ARM) from `.short` (size = 2). This is an
independently-correct, mainline-relevant assembler bug: current tinycc
carries the same grouping. tcc's own self-compilation emits no `.word`
inline asm, so the milestone-3 boot2==boot3 fixpoint is unaffected by
this fix.
---
 tccasm.c | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/tccasm.c b/tccasm.c
index 9e0882d..0564773 100644
--- a/tccasm.c
+++ b/tccasm.c
@@ -580,6 +580,14 @@ static void asm_parse_directive(TCCState *s1, int global)
         size = 1;
         goto asm_data;
     case TOK_ASMDIR_word:
+#ifdef TCC_TARGET_ARM
+        /* On ARM (and per GNU as), ".word" is a 32-bit datum; only x86 treats
+           it as 16-bit. The fork inherited x86's size=2, which silently
+           truncated musl's `.word 0xe7f000f0` (a_crash) to 2 bytes and left
+           the section 2-byte-misaligned, corrupting later branch fixups. */
+        size = 4;
+        goto asm_data;
+#endif
     case TOK_ASMDIR_short:
         size = 2;
         goto asm_data;
-- 
